{
  "document_id": "luke-21",
  "title": "Luke 21",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "Oxford",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-heading-22",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "22"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "he also saw a poor widow put in two small copper coins."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "2 : The (Gk “lepton”) was of little monetary value (see 12.59n.)",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 2,
      "verse_end": 2
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "He said, “Truly I tell you, this poor widow has put in more than all of them;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "for all of them have contributed out of their abundance, but she out of her poverty has put in all she had to live on.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-2",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.1–4: The widow's offering (Mk 12.41–44).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 4
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "When some were speaking about the temple, how it was adorned with beautiful stones and gifts dedicated to God, he said,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "“As for these things that you see, the days will come when not one stone will be left upon another; all will be thrown down.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-5",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.5–6: Foretelling the destruction of the Temple (Mt 24.1–2; Mk 13.1–2). Luke's version of the eschatological discourse in Mk 13 extends the time span between Jesus's day and the end time.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 5,
      "verse_end": 6
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-6",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "6 : See 19.44n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 6,
      "verse_end": 6
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "They asked him, “Teacher, when will this be, and what will be the sign that this is about to take place?”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-8",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "7 : 17.20; Acts 1.6.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 7
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "And he said, “Beware that you are not led astray; for many will come in my name and say, ‘I am he!’ and, ‘The time is near!’ Do not go after them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "“When you hear of wars and insurrections, do not be terrified; for these things must take place first, but the end will not follow immediately.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Then he said to them, “Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-9",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10 :",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 10,
      "verse_end": 10
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "there will be great earthquakes, and in various places famines and plagues; and there will be dreadful portents and great signs from heaven."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-7",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.7–11: Sayings about end-time signs (Mt 24.3–8; Mk 13.3–8).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 11
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "“But before all this occurs, they will arrest you and persecute you; they will hand you over to synagogues and prisons, and you will be brought before kings and governors because of my name."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "This will give you an opportunity to testify."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "So make up your minds not to prepare your defense in advance;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "for I will give you words and a wisdom that none of your opponents will be able to withstand or contradict."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-11",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "14–15 : 12.11–12. Anticipates the theme of divine assistance in Acts (e.g., 5.19–20; 12.6–11; 16.25–34).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 14,
      "verse_end": 15
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "You will be betrayed even by parents and brothers, by relatives and friends; and they will put some of you to death."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "You will be hated by all because of my name."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "But not a hair of your head will perish."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-12",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "18 : See 12.7; Acts 27.34; 1 Sam 14.45.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 18,
      "verse_end": 18
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "By your endurance you will gain your souls."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-10",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.12–19: Foretelling the persecution of the disciples (Mt 24.9–14; Mk 13.9–13).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 12,
      "verse_end": 19
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "“When you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then know that its desolation has come near."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Then those in Judea must flee to the mountains, and those inside the city must leave it, and those out in the country must not enter it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "for these are days of vengeance, as a fulfillment of all that is written."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-14",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "20–22 : 19.41–44; 23.28–31; 17.31.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 20,
      "verse_end": 22
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-15",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "22 : Cf. Isa 63.4; Jer 5.29; Hos 9.7.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 22,
      "verse_end": 22
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Woe to those who are pregnant and to those who are nursing infants in those days! For there will be great distress on the earth and wrath against this people;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "they will fall by the edge of the sword and be taken away as captives among all nations; and Jerusalem will be trampled on by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-13",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.20–24: The desolation of Jerusalem (Mt 24.15–22; Mk 13.14–20). See 19.41–44n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 20,
      "verse_end": 24
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-16",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "24 : Isa 63.18; Dan 8.13. may imply a divinely imposed limit on Roman dominance, or the extension of salvation to all nations (20.16).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 24,
      "verse_end": 24
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "“There will be signs in the sun, the moon, and the stars, and on the earth distress among nations confused by the roaring of the sea and the waves."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-19",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "25 : Isa 13.10; Joel 2.10; Zeph 1.15.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 25,
      "verse_end": 25
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "People will faint from fear and foreboding of what is coming upon the world, for the powers of the heavens will be shaken."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-20",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "26 : Cf. Isa 34.4. , the celestial bodies (v. 25).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 26,
      "verse_end": 26
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "Then they will see ‘the Son of Man coming in a cloud’ with power and great glory."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-18",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "25–27 : See Joel 3.3–4; Isa 24.19 (LXX); Pss 65.7; 46.3; 89.9; Wis 5.22; Jon 1.15.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 25,
      "verse_end": 27
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-21",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "27 : See Dan 7.13–14.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 27,
      "verse_end": 27
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Now when these things begin to take place, stand up and raise your heads, because your redemption is drawing near.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-17",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.25–28: The coming of the Son of Man (Mt 24.29–31; Mk 13.24–27).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 25,
      "verse_end": 28
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Then he told them a parable: “Look at the fig tree and all the trees;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "as soon as they sprout leaves you can see for yourselves and know that summer is already near."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "So also, when you see these things taking place, you know that the kingdom of God is near."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "Truly I tell you, this generation will not pass away until all things have taken place."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-23",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "32 : Cf. 9.27.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 32,
      "verse_end": 32
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-22",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.29–33: The lesson of the fig tree (Mt 24.32–36; Mk 13.28–32).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 29,
      "verse_end": 33
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-24",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "33 : 16.17.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 33,
      "verse_end": 33
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "“Be on guard so that your hearts are not weighed down with dissipation and drunkenness and the worries of this life, and that day does not catch you unexpectedly,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-27",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "34 : 8.14; 12.22; 1 Thess 5.6–7.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 34,
      "verse_end": 34
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "like a trap. For it will come upon all who live on the face of the whole earth."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "Be alert at all times, praying that you may have the strength to escape all these things that will take place, and to stand before the Son of Man.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-25",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.34–36: Admonition to alertness (cf. Mt 24.43–51; 25.13; Mk 13.33–37).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 34,
      "verse_end": 36
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-26",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "34–36 : 12.35–48.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 34,
      "verse_end": 36
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-28",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "36 : 2 Cor 5.10.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 36,
      "verse_end": 36
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "Every day he was teaching in the temple, and at night he would go out and spend the night on the Mount of Olives, as it was called."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-30",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "37 : , key locale in the passion narrative (22.39, 47–53).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 37,
      "verse_end": 37
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "And all the people would get up early in the morning to listen to him in the temple."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "19.28–21.38: Jesus's ministry in Jerusalem (Mt 21–24; Mk 11–13).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 38
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-29",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21.37–38: Summary concerning Jesus's ministry in Jerusalem.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 37,
      "verse_end": 38
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-luke-21-h1kj-31",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "38 : Jn 8.1–11 appears after this verse in some manuscripts; see Jn 8.11, note",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "luke",
        "chapter": 21
      },
      "verse_start": 38,
      "verse_end": 38
    }
  ]
}